= Introduction

This document outlines the requirements and specifications for the English Center Management Website. It details the functional and non-functional requirements, system architecture, and other essential information for the development and testing of the platform. The goal of this project is to create a comprehensive web-based solution to streamline the management of courses, students, teachers, and administrative tasks for an English language center.

== Purpose
This Software Requirements Specification (SRS) document is to outline the software requirements for the "Xây dựng website quản lí trung tâm tiếng Anh" (Building a website to manage an English center) project. This document provides a detailed technical foundation for the deployment, development, and operation of the website. It serves as a comprehensive guide for developers to plan, assign tasks, and implement the application. Additionally, testers will utilize this document to design test cases that align with the specified requirements, ensuring the final product meets quality standards and user expectations.

== Scope
This document covers the Website for Managing an English Center, which is part of the broader initiative to improve the center's management through a digital solution.

== Intended Audiences and Document Organization
This document is intended for:
- *Development team:* Responsible to develop detailed design, implement and perform unit test, integration test and system test for the application.
- *Data Migration team:* Responsible for creating data migration scripts and performing data migration for the application.
- *Documentation Team:* Responsible for writing User Guide for the application.
- *UAT team:* Responsible for conducting user acceptance test sessions with end users.

